.TH "fsl_asoc_get_dma_channel" 9 "fsl_asoc_get_dma_channel" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_asoc_get_dma_channel \- determine the dma channel for a SSI node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsl_asoc_get_dma_channel
.BI "(struct device_node *ssi_np "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct snd_soc_dai_link *dai "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *dma_channel_id "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *dma_id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ssi_np" 12
pointer to the SSI device tree node
.IP "name" 12
name of the phandle pointing to the dma channel
.IP "dai" 12
ASoC DAI link pointer to be filled with platform_name
.IP "dma_channel_id" 12
dma channel id to be returned
.IP "dma_id" 12
dma id to be returned
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function determines the dma and channel id for given SSI node.  It
also discovers the platform_name for the ASoC DAI link.
